---
import PageShell from '../../../../components/PageShell.astro';
import ComparisonTable from '../../../../components/ComparisonTable.astro';

const tocItems = [
  { id: 'overview', text: 'Overview', level: 2 },
  { id: 'healthcare-system', text: 'Healthcare System', level: 2 },
  { id: 'visa-requirements', text: 'Visa Options', level: 2 },
  { id: 'insurance-requirements', text: 'Insurance Requirements', level: 2 },
  { id: 'recommended-providers', text: 'Recommended Providers', level: 2 },
  { id: 'costs', text: 'Expected Costs', level: 2 },
  { id: 'scenarios', text: 'Real-World Scenarios', level: 2 },
  { id: 'faqs', text: 'Common Questions', level: 2 },
];

const relatedLinks = [
  { title: 'Namibia Insurance Guide', href: '/countries/namibia/insurance' },
  { title: 'Insurance for Seniors', href: '/insurance-for/seniors' },
  { title: 'South Africa for Seniors', href: '/insurance-for/seniors/in/south-africa' },
  { title: 'Botswana for Seniors', href: '/insurance-for/seniors/in/botswana' },
  { title: 'Zimbabwe for Seniors', href: '/insurance-for/seniors/in/zimbabwe' },
];

const providerColumns = [
  { key: 'provider', header: 'Provider' },
  { key: 'entryAge', header: 'Max Entry Age' },
  { key: 'renewal', header: 'Renewal' },
  { key: 'monthlyFrom', header: 'From (65-69)' },
  { key: 'namibiaFit', header: 'Namibia Fit' },
];

const providerRows = [
  { provider: 'Cigna Global', entryAge: '74', renewal: 'Lifetime', monthlyFrom: 'NAD$8,900-12,715/mo', namibiaFit: 'Excellent' },
  { provider: 'BUPA Global', entryAge: '79', renewal: 'Lifetime', monthlyFrom: 'NAD$10,400-14,870/mo', namibiaFit: 'Excellent' },
  { provider: 'Allianz Care', entryAge: '74', renewal: 'Lifetime', monthlyFrom: 'NAD$8,000-11,430/mo', namibiaFit: 'Very Good' },
  { provider: 'Now Health', entryAge: '74', renewal: 'Lifetime', monthlyFrom: 'NAD$7,450-10,640/mo', namibiaFit: 'Very Good' },
  { provider: 'Local (Momentum, Discovery)', entryAge: 'Varies', renewal: 'Annual', monthlyFrom: 'NAD$2,500-6,000/mo', namibiaFit: 'Regional' },
];

const costColumns = [
  { key: 'category', header: 'Expense' },
  { key: 'monthly', header: 'Monthly' },
  { key: 'annual', header: 'Annual' },
];

const costRows = [
  { category: 'International Insurance (65-69)', monthly: 'NAD$8,000-12,715', annual: 'NAD$96K-152.5K' },
  { category: 'International Insurance (70-74)', monthly: 'NAD$10,980-16,940', annual: 'NAD$131.8K-203.3K' },
  { category: 'International Insurance (75-79)', monthly: 'NAD$14,760-22,750', annual: 'NAD$177.1K-273K' },
  { category: 'Private Hospital Visit', monthly: 'NAD$500-1,500/visit', annual: 'Moderate' },
  { category: 'Private Hospital Stay', monthly: 'NAD$3,000-8,000/day', annual: 'Per incident' },
];
---

<PageShell
  title="Health Insurance for Seniors in Namibia 2026 | Retirement Guide"
  description="Guide to health insurance for seniors retiring in Namibia. Stunning deserts, German heritage, safari wildlife, and coverage for expats 65+."
  headline="Health Insurance for Seniors in Namibia"
  subheadline="Namibia offers stunning desert landscapes, German colonial heritage, excellent wildlife, and one of Africa's most stable democracies—a unique blend of European efficiency and African adventure."
  heroImage="/images/countries/namibia-hero-bg.png"
  tocItems={tocItems}
  relatedLinks={relatedLinks}
  ctaButtonText="Compare Senior Plans →"
  ctaButtonHref="/go/cigna-global"
>
  <h2 id="overview">Why Seniors Choose Namibia</h2>
  <p>
    Namibia offers stunning Sossusvlei dunes, Etosha wildlife, German colonial heritage, English as official language, and one of Africa's most stable democracies. For adventurous retirees seeking dramatic landscapes with European efficiency, Namibia provides unique African experience.
  </p>

  <p>
    Windhoek is the capital with best healthcare and German-influenced culture. Swakopmund offers coastal German town atmosphere. Etosha provides safari access. Most expats choose Windhoek for healthcare; Swakopmund for coastal lifestyle; Etosha region for wildlife.
  </p>

  <div class="bg-primary-50 border border-primary-200 rounded-lg p-6 my-6">
    <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-primary-900 mb-3">Key Facts for Seniors</h3>
    <ul class="text-primary-800 space-y-2">
      <li><strong>Healthcare:</strong> Good for Africa; South Africa backup</li>
      <li><strong>Language:</strong> English (official); German; Afrikaans</li>
      <li><strong>Cost of Living:</strong> NAD$15,000-30,000/month (~$830-1,660 USD); moderate</li>
      <li><strong>Climate:</strong> Desert; mild; very dry</li>
      <li><strong>Character:</strong> German efficiency; African landscape</li>
      <li><strong>South Africa ties:</strong> Currency pegged; healthcare backup</li>
    </ul>
  </div>

  <h2 id="healthcare-system">Namibia Healthcare System</h2>
  <p>
    Namibia healthcare is good for Africa—Medi-Clinic Windhoek and Rhino Park Private Hospital provide modern care. German-influenced efficiency. Many doctors trained in South Africa or Europe. Complex cases may need Cape Town or Johannesburg (2-hour flights).
  </p>

  <p>
    Private healthcare in Windhoek is good. Public system functional but limited. Remote areas have minimal healthcare. International insurance with South Africa evacuation recommended. Currency pegged to South African rand.
  </p>

  <div class="bg-amber-50 border border-amber-200 rounded-lg p-4 my-6">
    <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-amber-900 mb-2">South Africa Backup</h3>
    <p class="text-amber-800 mb-0">
      South Africa provides medical backup—Cape Town and Johannesburg are 2-hour flights with world-class hospitals. Currency pegged to rand makes transactions easy. Include South Africa in insurance coverage for complex conditions.
    </p>
  </div>

  <h2 id="visa-requirements">Visa Options for Seniors</h2>
  <p>
    Namibia has accessible visa options:
  </p>

  <h3>Tourist Entry</h3>
  <p>
    90 days visa-free for many nationalities including US, EU, UK, Commonwealth. Extensions available.
  </p>

  <h3>Temporary Residence</h3>
  <p>
    For stays over 90 days. Various categories including retirement. Apply through Home Affairs.
  </p>

  <h3>Work Permit</h3>
  <p>
    For employment. Some semi-retired professionals use this with tourism businesses.
  </p>

  <h3>Permanent Residence</h3>
  <p>
    After 5 years. Investment options available. Namibia welcomes foreign investment.
  </p>

  <h2 id="insurance-requirements">Insurance Requirements</h2>
  <p>
    Insurance requirements for Namibia:
  </p>

  <ul>
    <li><strong>Entry:</strong> Travel insurance recommended</li>
    <li><strong>Residence:</strong> Health insurance recommended</li>
    <li><strong>Practical:</strong> International coverage strongly recommended</li>
    <li><strong>Evacuation:</strong> South Africa coverage important</li>
  </ul>

  <div class="bg-blue-50 border border-blue-200 rounded-lg p-4 my-6">
    <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-blue-900 mb-2">Insurance Strategy for Namibia</h3>
    <p class="text-blue-800 mb-0">
      International insurance with South Africa coverage recommended. Windhoek private hospitals handle routine care well. Cape Town/Johannesburg provide specialist backup. South African medical aids sometimes work in Namibia. Currency peg simplifies finances.
    </p>
  </div>

  <h2 id="recommended-providers">Recommended Insurance Providers</h2>
  <p>
    For seniors in Namibia, South Africa network important:
  </p>

  <ComparisonTable columns={providerColumns} rows={providerRows} />

  <h3>Why These Providers Work for Namibia</h3>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Cigna Global:</strong> Strong Southern Africa network</li>
    <li><strong>BUPA Global:</strong> Highest entry age (79), comprehensive</li>
    <li><strong>South Africa access:</strong> World-class healthcare nearby</li>
    <li><strong>German efficiency:</strong> Good local private care</li>
  </ul>

  <div class="bg-primary-50 border border-primary-200 rounded-lg p-6 my-8">
    <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">Get Personalized Senior Quotes</h3>
    <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-4">Compare coverage with South Africa network.</p>
    <div class="flex flex-wrap gap-3">
      <a href="/go/cigna-global" class="inline-block px-5 py-2.5 bg-primary-600 text-white rounded-lg hover:bg-primary-700 transition-colors font-medium" style="color: white !important;">Get Cigna Quote</a>
      <a href="/go/bupa-global" class="inline-block px-5 py-2.5 bg-neutral-700 text-white rounded-lg hover:bg-neutral-800 transition-colors font-medium" style="color: white !important;">Get BUPA Quote</a>
    </div>
  </div>

  <h2 id="costs">Expected Insurance Costs</h2>
  <p>
    Insurance costs for Namibia (NAD pegged 1:1 to ZAR, ~18 to USD):
  </p>

  <ComparisonTable columns={costColumns} rows={costRows} />

  <h3>Cost-Saving Strategies</h3>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Windhoek base:</strong> Best local healthcare</li>
    <li><strong>South Africa network:</strong> Use for complex care</li>
    <li><strong>High deductible:</strong> Private care affordable</li>
    <li><strong>Regional plans:</strong> Southern Africa focused</li>
  </ul>

  <h2 id="scenarios">Real-World Scenarios</h2>

  <div class="space-y-6 my-8">
    <div class="bg-neutral-50 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-3">Scenario 1: German Retiree, 68</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-2"><strong>Situation:</strong> €2,500/month pension. Temp residence. Swakopmund.</p>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-2"><strong>Solution:</strong> Cigna Global with Europe and Africa coverage.</p>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0"><strong>Cost:</strong> ~NAD$9,500/month (~$525). German heritage; comprehensive backup.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="bg-neutral-50 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-3">Scenario 2: South African Neighbor, 71</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-2"><strong>Situation:</strong> ZAR$40,000/month pension. Residence permit. Windhoek.</p>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-2"><strong>Solution:</strong> BUPA Global with South Africa home coverage.</p>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0"><strong>Cost:</strong> ~NAD$12,000/month (~$665). Border ease; home backup.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="bg-neutral-50 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-3">Scenario 3: Desert Photography Enthusiast, 66</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-2"><strong>Situation:</strong> $2,500/month income. Tourist visa rotation. Sossusvlei area.</p>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-2"><strong>Solution:</strong> Allianz Care with evacuation to Windhoek/South Africa.</p>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0"><strong>Cost:</strong> ~NAD$8,000/month (~$445). Remote access; comprehensive backup.</p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <h2 id="faqs">Common Questions</h2>

  <div class="space-y-6 my-8">
    <div class="border-b border-neutral-200 pb-4">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">Is Namibia really German?</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0">
        German heritage strong—former German colony until 1915. German architecture, language, food (especially Swakopmund). German widely spoken. Efficient administration. But majority population is African with diverse ethnic groups. Unique blend.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="border-b border-neutral-200 pb-4">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">What languages work?</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0">
        English is official—works everywhere. German widely spoken in tourism, business, healthcare. Afrikaans common. Indigenous languages too. English speakers won't have problems. German is bonus.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="border-b border-neutral-200 pb-4">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">Is Namibia safe?</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0">
        Very safe—one of Africa's safest countries. Low crime compared to neighbors. Safe for self-driving. Tourist areas very secure. Normal precautions in cities. Overall excellent safety record.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="border-b border-neutral-200 pb-4">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">What about the desert climate?</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0">
        Very dry—one of driest countries. Windhoek has pleasant highland climate. Coast has cool foggy mornings. Interior gets hot. Low humidity is comfortable. Not tropical heat. Water scarcity is real issue.
      </p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="bg-primary-50 border border-primary-200 rounded-lg p-6 my-8">
    <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">Ready to Compare Options?</h3>
    <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-4">Get quotes from providers for Namibia coverage.</p>
    <div class="flex flex-wrap gap-3">
      <a href="/go/cigna-global" class="inline-block px-5 py-2.5 bg-primary-600 text-white rounded-lg hover:bg-primary-700 transition-colors font-medium" style="color: white !important;">Get Cigna Quote</a>
      <a href="/go/allianz-care" class="inline-block px-5 py-2.5 bg-neutral-700 text-white rounded-lg hover:bg-neutral-800 transition-colors font-medium" style="color: white !important;">Get Allianz Quote</a>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="bg-neutral-50 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6 mt-8">
    <p class="text-sm text-neutral-600 mb-0">
      <strong>Disclaimer:</strong> This guide is for informational purposes only. Insurance requirements, visa regulations, and healthcare access rules change regularly. Always verify current requirements with Namibia authorities and consult with a licensed insurance professional.
    </p>
  </div>
</PageShell>
